## Windows Update Repair and System Integrity Recovery Script

## This script automates a full reset and repair process for Windows Update components and related system services. It is designed to resolve common update failures caused by corrupted update cache, broken service registrations, or system component inconsistencies.

## The script performs the following actions:

1. Stops key Windows Update-related services (Windows Update, BITS, Cryptographic Services, and MSI Installer)
2. Renames the SoftwareDistribution and Catroot2 folders to force regeneration of update cache files
3. Restarts all previously stopped services to restore normal update functionality
4. Clears residual cached update files from renamed directories
5. Re-registers critical Windows Update and system DLL components using regsvr32
6. Resets Winsock and proxy configurations to repair network-related update issues
7. Executes system integrity and repair tools:
8. System File Checker (sfc /scannow)
9. DISM health checks and image repair (CheckHealth, ScanHealth, RestoreHealth, and component cleanup)


@echo off
echo Stopping Windows Update services...
net stop wuauserv
net stop cryptSvc
net stop bits
net stop msiserver
echo Renaming SoftwareDistribution and Catroot2 folders...
ren C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution SoftwareDistribution.old
ren C:\Windows\System32\catroot2 Catroot2.old
echo Restarting Windows Update services...
net start wuauserv
net start cryptSvc
net start bits
net start msiserver
echo Clearing the update cache...
del /q /s C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution.old\*.*
del /q /s C:\Windows\System32\Catroot2.old\*.* 
echo Registering Windows Update DLLs...
regsvr32.exe /s wuaueng.dll
regsvr32.exe /s wuapi.dll
regsvr32.exe /s wups.dll
regsvr32.exe /s wucltux.dll
regsvr32.exe /s wuwebv.dll
regsvr32.exe /s jscript.dll
regsvr32.exe /s msxml3.dll
regsvr32.exe /s atl.dll
regsvr32.exe /s softpub.dll
regsvr32.exe /s urlmon.dll
regsvr32.exe /s mshtml.dll
netsh winsock reset
netsh winsock reset proxy
echo Performing SFC scan...
sfc /scannow
dism.exe /Online /Cleanup-image /CheckHealth
dism.exe /Online /Cleanup-image /ScanHealth
dism /Online /Cleanup-image /StartComponentCleanup
dism.exe /Online /Cleanup-image /RestoreHealth
echo Windows Update troubleshooting complete.
